e job requirements and candidate background.\\n    a. Prepare a set of technical interview questions tailored to the job requirements (extracted in step 1) and the candidate's skills and experience (extracted in step 2).\\n    b. Ask the candidate the prepared technical questions.\\n    c. Record the candidate's responses for each question.\\n4. Send emails as needed during the interview process.\\n    a. Send a confirmation email to the candidate before the interview with details such as time, date, and meeting link.\\n    b. Send a thank-you email to the candidate after the interview.\\n5. Score candidate responses based on predefined criteria and benchmarks.\\n    a. For each question, evaluate the candidate's response based on its correctness, completeness, and clarity.\\n    b. Assign a score (e.g., on a scale of 1 to 10) to each response.\\n    c. Document the rationale for each score, highlighting the strengths and weaknesses of the response.\\n6. Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's performance.\\n    a. Include the job requirements, candidate background, interview questions, candidate responses, and scores.\\n    b. Provide an overall assessment of the candidate's suitability for the role based on their technical skills, experience, and communication abilities.\\n    c. Recommend whether to proceed with the candidate to the next stage of the interview process or not.\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The output is in plain text rather than the required JSON format.\\n- It lists high-level interview steps but does not define a clear algorithm for generating tailored questions.\\n- It lacks details on input/output schemas, data structures, and selection logic.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"algorithm_name\\\": \\\"TailoredTechnicalQuestionGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Generate a tailored set of tech