red_skills and candidate_skills.\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"skill_gaps\\\": [\\\"string\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 4,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"FilterQuestionBank\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Select questions whose tags intersect with required_skills or skill_gaps.\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"relevant_question_ids\\\": [\\\"string\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 5,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ScoreAndRankQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Compute a relevance score for each relevant question based on tag matches and difficulty.\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters\\\": {\\n        \\\"tag_weight\\\": 2,\\n        \\\"difficulty_weight\\\": {\\\"Easy\\\": 1, \\\"Medium\\\": 2, \\\"Hard\\\": 3}\\n      },\\n      \\\"score_formula\\\": \\\"score = (matching_tag_count * tag_weight) + difficulty_weight[difficulty]\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"ranked_questions\\\": [\\n          {\\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"score\\\": \\\"number\\\"}\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 6,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"SelectTopQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Choose the top_n questions by highest score.\\\",\\n      \\\"input_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"ranked_questions\\\": [\\\"{id, score}\\\"],\\n        \\\"top_n\\\": \\\"number\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"selected_question_ids\\\": [\\\"string\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 7,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"CustomizeQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Personalize each selected question by referencing candidate experience where relevant.\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"tailored_questions\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n            \\\"reason\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"OutputResult\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Return the tailored_questions array as the final output.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:11:34,340", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Develop algorithm to\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 5,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```txt\\n1. Analyze the job description using the `parse_job_description` function from task0 and store the extracted job data in a dictionary.\\n2. Analyze the candidate resume using the `ResumeParser` class from task1, parse the resume text, and store the extracted profile data in a dictionary.\\n3. Conduct a technical interview using the interview execution component (task3) based on the job requirements and candidate background.\\n    a. Prepare a set of technical interview questions tailored to the job requirements (extracted in step 1) and the candidate's skills and experience (extracted in step 2).\\n    b. Ask the candidate the prepared technical questions.\\n    c. Record the candidate's responses for each question.\\n4. Send emails as needed during the interview process.\\n    a. Send a confirmation email to the candidate before the interview with details such as time, date, and meeting link.\\n    b. Send a thank-you email to the candidate after the interview.\\n5. Score candidate responses based on predefined criteria and benchmarks.\\n    a. For each question, evaluate the candidate's response based on its correctness, completeness, and clarity.\\n    b. Assign a score (e.g., on a scale of 1 to 10) to each response.\\n    c. Document the rationale for each score, highlighting the strengths and weaknesses of the response.\\n6. Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's performance.\\n    a. Include the job requirements, candidate background, interview questions, candidate responses, and scores.\\n    b. Provide an overall assessment of the candidate's suitability for the role based on their technical skills, experience, and communication abilities.\\n    c. Recommend whether to proceed with the candidate to the next stage of the interview process or not.\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The output is in plain text rather than the required JSON format.\\n- It lists high-level interview steps but does not define a clear algorithm for generating tailored questions.\\n- It lacks details on input/output schemas, data structures, and selection logic.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"algorithm_name\\\": \\\"TailoredTechnicalQuestionGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions based on job requirements and candidate background.\\\",\\n  \\\"inputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_description\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\n    \\\"candidate_resume\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"question_bank\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between threads and processes.\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"Concurrency\\\", \\\"OS\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\"\\n      }\\n      // … additional questions\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"outputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"tailored_questions\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between threads and processes.\\\",\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n        \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Matches required system-level concurrency skill; not yet present on candidate resume\\\"\\n      }\\n      // … selected questions\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ParseJobDescription\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Use NLP to extract required skills, technologies, and proficiency levels from job_description.\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"Concurrency\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\"],\\n        \\\"levels\\\": {\\\"Java\\\": \\\"Senior\\\", \\\"Concurrency\\\": \\\"Intermediate\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\": \\\"Senior\\\"}\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 2,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ParseCandidateResume\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Use resume parser to extract candidate's skills, experiences, and projects.\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"Spring Boot\\\"],\\n        \\\"projects\\\": [\\\"E-commerce platform\\\", \\\"Chat application\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 3,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"IdentifySkillGaps\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Compare required_skills with candidate_skills to find missing or weak areas.\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"gaps\\\": [\\\"Concurrency\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 4,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"FilterQuestionBank\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Select questions whose tags intersect with required_skills or gaps.\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_relevant_questions\\\": [\\\"Q1\\\", \\\"Q5\\\", \\\"Q12\\\", \\\"Q20\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 5,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ScoreAndRankQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"For each candidate_relevant_question, compute a relevance score:\\\",\\n      \\\"score_formula\\\": \\\"score = tag_match_count * weight_skill + difficulty_weight + novelty_bonus\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters\\\": {\\n        \\\"weight_skill\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"difficulty_weight\\\": {\\\"Easy\\\": 1, \\\"Medium\\\": 2, \\\"Hard\\\": 3},\\n        \\\"novelty_bonus\\\": 2\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"ranked_questions\\\": [\\n          {\\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\", \\\"score\\\": 12},\\n          {\\\"id\\\": \\\"Q5\\\", \\\"score\\\": 10},\\n          {\\\"id\\\": \\\"Q12\\\", \\\"score\\\": 9},\\n          {\\\"id\\\": \\\"Q20\\\", \\\"score\\\": 8}\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 6,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"SelectTopNQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Pick the top N questions to meet desired interview length and coverage.\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters\\\": {\\n        \\\"N\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"coverage\\\": {\\\"skills\\\": 3, \\\"difficulty_levels\\\": 2}\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"selected_question_ids\\\": [\\\"Q1\\\", \\\"Q5\\\", \\\"Q12\\\", \\\"Q20\\\", \\\"Q7\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 7,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"CustomizeQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Personalize questions by referencing candidate projects or experience where appropriate.\\\",\\n      \\\"example\\\": \\\"If Q1 is about Concurrency, append: '...consider your chat application project context.'\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"tailored_questions\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between threads and processes. In your chat application project, how did you manage concurrency?\\\",\\n            \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n            \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Address missing concurrency skill and tie to candidate’s prior work\\\"\\n          }\\n          // … other questions\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"OutputResult\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Return the tailored_questions array as the final output.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 1\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"algorithm_name\\\": \\\"TailoredTechnicalInterviewProcess\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"End-to-end algorithm for conducting a tailored technical interview, scoring candidate responses, and generating an evaluation report.\\\",\\n  \\\"inputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_description\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"candidate_resume\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"question_bank\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of inheritance in object-oriented programming.\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"OOP\\\", \\\"Java\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Technical\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q2\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Describe the difference between REST and GraphQL.\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"API\\\", \\\"Web Services\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Technical\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q3\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"How do you handle concurrency in Python?\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"Concurrency\\\", \\\"Python\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Hard\\\",\\n        \\\"category\\\": \\\"Technical\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"outputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"interview_transcript\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of inheritance in object-oriented programming.\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"Inheritance is when a class inherits properties and methods from a parent class...\\\",\\n        \\\"score\\\": 7,\\n        \\\"rationale\\\": \\\"Good understanding of the concept but lacked detail on multiple inheritance.\\\",\\n        \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\\"Can you give an example of multiple inheritance?\\\", \\\"What are some disadvantages of using inheritance?\\\"]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"evaluation_report\\\": {\\n      \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n      \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n      \\\"overall_score\\\": 7.5,\\n      \\\"recommendation\\\": \\\"Proceed to the next round.\\\",\\n      \\\"strengths\\\": [\\\"Strong understanding of core OOP concepts.\\\", \\\"Good communication skills.\\\"],\\n      \\\"weaknesses\\\": [\\\"Limited knowledge of advanced concurrency patterns.\\\"],\\n      \\\"summary\\\": \\\"John demonstrated a solid understanding of fundamental software engineering principles but needs further evaluation on system design and problem-solving skills.\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ExtractJobRequirements\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Parse the job description to extract job title, required skills, experience level, and responsibilities.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": \\\"job_description\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"Python\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\"],\\n        \\\"experience_level\\\": \\\"Mid-Level\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\\"Develop and maintain web applications\\\", \\\"Write and test code\\\"]\\n      },\\n      \\\"function_call\\\": \\\"parse_job_description(job_description)\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 2,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ExtractCandidateProfile\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Parse the candidate's resume to extract name, contact information, skills, and experience.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": \\\"candidate_resume\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        \\\"email\\\": \\\"john.doe@example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Spring Boot\\\", \\\"Git\\\"],\\n        \\\"experience\\\": [\\\"Software Engineer at ABC Corp\\\"]\\n      },\\n      \\\"function_call\\\": \\\"ResumeParser(candidate_resume).parse()\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 3,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"GenerateTailoredQuestions\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Generate a list of technical interview questions based on the job requirements and candidate's skills. Prioritize questions related to skill gaps.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": {\\n        \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"Python\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\"],\\n        \\\"candidate_skills\\\": [\\\"Java\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"Spring Boot\\\", \\\"Git\\\"],\\n        \\\"question_bank\\\": \\\"question_bank\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": {\\n        \\\"tailored_questions\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q2\\\",\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Describe the difference between REST and GraphQL.\\\",\\n            \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Assess understanding of API concepts, a required skill not explicitly mentioned in the resume.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\\"What are the pros and cons of each approach?\\\", \\\"In what scenarios would you choose one over the other?\\\"]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q3\\\",\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"How do you handle concurrency in Python?\\\",\\n            \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Assess knowledge of concurrency which is important for scalable applications.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\\"What are the common pitfalls?\\\", \\\"Give examples from your experience.\\\"]\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      \\\"algorithm\\\": \\\"Select questions from question_bank that cover required skills, especially those not listed in candidate_skills. Prioritize questions with higher difficulty and relevance scores based on the job requirements.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 4,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"SendInterviewConfirmationEmail\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Send an email to the candidate confirming the interview details (date, time, meeting link).\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        \\\"email\\\": \\\"john.doe@example.com\\\",\\n        \\\"interview_time\\\": \\\"2024-01-16 10:00 AM\\\",\\n        \\\"meeting_link\\\": \\\"https://example.com/interview\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": \\\"Email sent successfully.\\\",\\n      \\\"email_template\\\": \\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\\\n\\\\nThis email confirms your technical interview on {interview_time} at {meeting_link}.\\\\n\\\\nBest regards,\\\\nThe Hiring Team\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 5,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ConductTechnicalInterview\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Conduct the technical interview by asking the tailored questions and recording the candidate's responses.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": {\\n        \\\"tailored_questions\\\": \\\"tailored_questions\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": \\\"interview_transcript\\\",\\n      \\\"process\\\": \\\"For each question in tailored_questions, ask the question to the candidate, record their response, and note any follow-up questions asked.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 6,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ScoreCandidateResponses\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Evaluate the candidate's responses based on predefined criteria and benchmarks. Assign a score to each response and document the rationale.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": \\\"interview_transcript\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": \\\"interview_transcript (with scores and rationales)\\\",\\n      \\\"scoring_criteria\\\": {\\n        \\\"Correctness\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"Completeness\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Clarity\\\": 2,\\n        \\\"ProblemSolving\\\": 1\\n      },\\n      \\\"benchmarks\\\": {\\n        \\\"Q2\\\": \\\"A good answer would explain the architectural differences, data fetching approaches, and use cases for REST and GraphQL.\\\",\\n        \\\"Q3\\\": \\\"Candidate should mention threading, multiprocessing, asyncio, and GIL limitations in Python.\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"process\\\": \\\"For each question response in interview_transcript, evaluate against scoring_criteria and benchmarks. Provide a score (out of 10) and rationale.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 7,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"SendThankYouEmail\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Send a thank-you email to the candidate after the interview.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        \\\"email\\\": \\\"john.doe@example.com\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": \\\"Email sent successfully.\\\",\\n      \\\"email_template\\\": \\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\\\n\\\\nThank you for your time interviewing for the Software Engineer position. We will be in touch soon regarding the next steps.\\\\n\\\\nBest regards,\\\\nThe Hiring Team\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 8,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"GenerateEvaluationReport\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Generate a final evaluation report summarizing the candidate's performance, including overall score, strengths, weaknesses, and recommendation.\\\",\\n      \\\"input\\\": {\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        \\\"interview_transcript\\\": \\\"interview_transcript\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"output\\\": \\\"evaluation_report\\\",\\n      \\\"algorithm\\\": \\\"Calculate overall_score based on average of individual question scores. Identify strengths based on high-scoring responses. Identify weaknesses based on low-scoring responses and skill gaps. Provide a recommendation based on overall performance and alignment with job requirements.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 9,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"OutputResults\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Output the interview transcript and evaluation report.\\\",\\n      \\\"output\\\": [\\\"interview_transcript\\\", \\\"evaluation_report\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 1\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The JSON includes steps (sending emails, conducting interviews, scoring, reporting) beyond the current requirement, which is only to generate tailored technical questions.\\n- The “outputs” section contains interview transcripts and evaluation reports that are out of scope.\\n- The algorithm mixes multiple processes; it should focus solely on question generation.\\n- Missing explicit parameterization for number of questions (N) and lacks a clear scoring/ranking mechanism schema.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"algorithm_name\\\": \\\"TailoredTechnicalQuestionGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Generate a tailored set of technical interview questions by extracting job requirements and candidate background, identifying skill gaps, and selecting the most relevant questions from a question bank.\\\",\\n  \\\"inputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_description\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"candidate_resume\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"question_bank\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between threads and processes.\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"Concurrency\\\", \\\"OS\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q2\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Describe the use of RESTful APIs in microservices.\\\",\\n        \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"API\\\", \\\"Microservices\\\"],\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\"\\n      }\\n      // … additional questions\\n    ],\\n    \\\"parameters\\\": {\\n      \\\"top_n\\\": 5\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"outputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"tailored_questions\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"text\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between threads and processes.\\\",\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n        \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Assesses concurrency, a required skill missing on resume.\\\"\\n      }\\n      // … up to top_n questions\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ParseJobDescription\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Extract required skills and proficiency levels from the job_description using NLP.\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\\"string\\\"],\\n        \\\"proficiency\\\": {\\\"skill\\\": \\\"string\\\"}\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 2,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ParseCandidateResume\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Extract candidate_skills from candidate_resume using a resume parser.\\\",\\n      \\\"output_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_skills\\\": [\\\"string\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"step_number\\\": 3,\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"IdentifySkillGaps\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Compute the difference between requ