nd Spring Boot.\\n   - Lacks hands-on with newer frameworks (e.g., Micronaut).\\n\\n2) Problem Solving & Algorithms:      5/5\\n   - Efficient approach to array and tree problems.\\n   - Clear explanation of time/space complexity.\\n\\n3) System Design:                     3/5\\n   - Designed a scalable URL shortener.\\n   - Missing discussion on caching and message queuing.\\n\\n4) Communication & Collaboration:     4/5\\n   - Articulate and concise.\\n   - Good team-oriented examples.\\n\\nOverall Score (Average):              4.0/5\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n3. INTERVIEWER COMMENTS\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\n• Strengths:\\n  - Excellent algorithmic skills.\\n  - Good mastery of core backend concepts.\\n  - Strong communication and teamwork examples.\\n\\n• Areas for Improvement:\\n  - Expand experience with cloud-native patterns (e.g., Kafka, Redis).\\n  - Deepen understanding of distributed caching strategies.\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n4. RECOMMENDATION\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\nBased on the above evaluation, we recommend proceeding to:\\n  [ ] Offer Extension\\n  [X] Technical Lead Review\\n  [ ] Do Not Proceed\\n\\nRationale:\\n  John demonstrates solid backend fundamentals and problem-solving ability. A technical lead review will confirm cloud-architecture fit and align on tooling preferences before final offer.\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n5. NEXT STEPS & ACTION ITEMS\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\n1. Schedule a follow-up system design session with the Tech Lead.  \\n2. Share coding challenge environment details by June 15, 2024.  \\n3. Gather feedback from DevOps team on cloud deployment fit.\\n\\nReport generated by: Jane Smith  \\nDate: June 13, 2024  \\n```\"}"}
