view process log (Steps 1–6) plus the final report.\\n- The current task requires only the “FINAL EVALUATION REPORT” section in plain text as a .txt file.\\n- Please remove all steps and present only the final evaluation report.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```text\\n===============================\\nFINAL EVALUATION REPORT\\n===============================\\n\\nCandidate Name:       Arya Stark\\nCandidate Email:      arya.stark@example.com\\nPosition:             Data Scientist\\nInterview Date:       August 3, 2024\\nInterviewer:          Jon Snow, Lead Data Scientist\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n1. OVERVIEW\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\nArya Stark interviewed for the Data Scientist position. The interview covered:\\n  • Technical Knowledge (languages, libraries)\\n  • Problem Solving & Algorithms\\n  • Statistical Analysis\\n  • Communication & Collaboration\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n2. DETAILED SCORES\\n   (Scale: 1 = Poor, 5 = Excellent)\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\n1) Technical Knowledge:               4/5\\n   - Strong proficiency in Python, R, Pandas, NumPy, and Scikit-learn.\\n   - Limited experience with TensorFlow and Keras.\\n\\n2) Problem Solving & Algorithms:      5/5\\n   - Efficient and well-structured code.\\n   - Clear understanding of model evaluation metrics.\\n\\n3) Statistical Analysis:              4/5\\n   - Good understanding of hypothesis testing and A/B testing methodologies.\\n\\n4) Communication & Collaboration:     5/5\\n   - Articulate, concise, and team-oriented.\\n\\nOverall Score (Average):              4.5/5\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n3. INTERVIEWER COMMENTS\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\n• Strengths:\\n  - Excellent technical skills and problem-solving abilities.\\n  - Strong understanding of machine learning algorithms.\\n  - Effective communication and collaboration skills.\\n\\n• Areas for Improvement:\\n  - Gain experience with deep learning frameworks (TensorFlow, Keras).\\n  - Consider publishing research findings in peer-reviewed journals.\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n4. RECOMMENDATION\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\nBased on the above evaluation, we recommend:\\n  [X] Offer Extension\\n  [ ] Technical Lead Review\\n  [ ] Do Not Proceed\\n\\nRationale:\\n  Arya possesses the required technical skills, experience, and soft skills to excel in the Data Scientist position. Her strong understanding of machine learning techniques and statistical analysis makes her a valuable asset to the team.\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n5. NEXT STEPS & ACTION ITEMS\\n----------------------------------------------------------\\n\\n1. Extend an offer to Arya Stark for the Data Scientist position.  \\n2. Schedule a follow-up meeting to discuss compensation and benefits.  \\n3. Onboard Arya Stark to the team and provide necessary training resources.  \\n\\nReport generated by: Jon Snow  \\nDate: August 4, 2024  \\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\n\\nYour task is to take interview. The following are the steps\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Create scoring engine to evaluate and score candidate interview responses according to predefined criteria\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport argparse\\nimport json\\nimport os\\nimport sys\\nimport smtplib\\nimport re\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\n\\ndef log_step(log_path, message):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Append a timestamped step message to the steps log file.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    timestamp = datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \\\"Z\\\"\\n    with open(log_path, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as log_f:\\n        log_f.write(f\\\"[{timestamp}] {message}\\\\n\\\")\\n\\ndef analyze_job_description(job_description_path, steps_log_path):\\n    if not os.path.isfile(job_description_path):\\n        sys.exit(f\\\"Error: Job description file not found: {job_description_path}\\\")\\n    text = open(job_description_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8').read()\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Analyzed job description from {job_description_path}.\\\")\\n    return text\\n\\ndef analyze_resume(resume_path, steps_log_path):\\n    if not os.path.isfile(resume_path):\\n        sys.exit(f\\\"Error: Resume file not found: {resume_path}\\\")\\n    text = open(resume_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8').read()\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Analyzed resume from {resume_path}.\\\")\\n    return text\\n\\ndef conduct_technical_interview(job_description_path, resume_path, questions_path,\\n                                output_path, candidate_email, steps_log_path):\\n    open(steps_log_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8').close()  # reset log\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, \\\"Started interview execution.\\\")\\n\\n    jd = analyze_job_description(job_description_path, steps_log_path)\\n    res = analyze_resume(resume_path, steps_log_path)\\n\\n    if not os.path.isfile(questions_path):\\n        sys.exit(f\\\"Error: Questions file not found: {questions_path}\\\")\\n    questions = json.load(open(questions_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8'))\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Loaded {len(questions)} questions from {questions_path}.\\\")\\n\\n    # Notify candidate\\n    send_email(candidate_email, \\\"Interview Started\\\", \\\"Your technical interview has begun.\\\")\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Sent 'Interview Started' email to {candidate_email}.\\\")\\n\\n    interview_start = datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \\\"Z\\\"\\n    responses = []\\n    for idx, q in enumerate(questions, start=1):\\n        q_text = q.get(\\\"id\\\", f\\\"q{idx}\\\")  # allow an 'id' field\\n        question = q.get(\\\"text\\\") if isinstance(q, dict) else str(q)\\n        print(f\\\"\\\\nQuestion {idx}: {question}\\\")\\n        log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Asking question {q_text}.\\\")\\n        start_t = datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \\\"Z\\\"\\n        answer = input(\\\"Candidate response: \\\")\\n        end_t = datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \\\"Z\\\"\\n        log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Recorded response for {q_text}.\\\")\\n        responses.append({\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": q_text,\\n            \\\"question\\\": question,\\n            \\\"response\\\": answer,\\n            \\\"start_time\\\": start_t,\\n            \\\"end_time\\\": end_t\\n        })\\n\\n    interview_end = datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \\\"Z\\\"\\n    send_email(candidate_email, \\\"Interview Finished\\\", \\\"Thank you for completing the interview.\\\")\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Sent 'Interview Finished' email to {candidate_email}.\\\")\\n\\n    data = {\\n        \\\"job_description_path\\\": job_description_path,\\n        \\\"resume_path\\\": resume_path,\\n        \\\"questions_path\\\": questions_path,\\n        \\\"interview_start\\\": interview_start,\\n        \\\"interview_end\\\": interview_end,\\n        \\\"responses\\\": responses\\n    }\\n    json.dump(data, open(output_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8'), indent=2)\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Saved raw interview data to {output_path}.\\\")\\n    return data\\n\\ndef send_email(to_email, subject, body):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Sends an email notification (configure SMTP as needed).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    from_email = \\\"your_email@example.com\\\"\\n    from_pwd = \\\"your_password\\\"\\n    msg = MIMEText(body)\\n    msg['Subject'] = subject\\n    msg['From'] = from_email\\n    msg['To'] = to_email\\n    try:\\n        with smtplib.SMTP_SSL('smtp.gmail.com', 465) as smtp:\\n            smtp.login(from_email, from_pwd)\\n            smtp.send_message(msg)\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        print(f\\\"Warning: could not send email: {e}\\\")\\n\\ndef score_candidate_responses(interview_data, rubric_path, steps_log_path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Scoring rubric format (JSON):\\n    {\\n      \\\"questions\\\": {\\n        \\\"q1\\\": {\\n          \\\"max_score\\\": 5,\\n          \\\"keywords\\\": [\\\"function\\\", \\\"loop\\\", \\\"recursion\\\"]\\n        },\\n        \\\"data-structures\\\": {\\n          \\\"max_score\\\": 4,\\n          \\\"keywords\\\": [\\\"array\\\", \\\"stack\\\", \\\"queue\\\", \\\"tree\\\"]\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, \\\"Started scoring responses.\\\")\\n    rubric = json.load(open(rubric_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8'))\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Loaded rubric from {rubric_path}.\\\")\\n\\n    total_score = 0.0\\n    total_max = 0.0\\n    scored_list = []\\n\\n    for resp in interview_data.get(\\\"responses\\\", []):\\n        qid = resp[\\\"question_id\\\"]\\n        answer = resp[\\\"response\\\"].lower()\\n        crit = rubric.get(\\\"questions\\\", {}).get(qid)\\n\\n        if not crit:\\n            log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"No rubric for {qid}, score=0.\\\")\\n            score = 0.0\\n            max_score = 0.0\\n        else:\\n            keywords = crit.get(\\\"keywords\\\", [])\\n            max_score = crit.get(\\\"max_score\\\", 0)\\n            matches = 0\\n            for kw in keywords:\\n                if re.search(rf\\\"\\\\b{re.escape(kw.lower())}\\\\b\\\", answer):\\n                    matches += 1\\n                    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Matched '{kw}' in {qid}.\\\")\\n            score = round((matches / len(keywords)) * max_score, 2) if keywords else 0.0\\n            log_step(steps_log_path,\\n                     f\\\"{qid}: matched {matches}/{len(keywords)}, assigned {score}/{max_score}.\\\")\\n\\n        total_score += score\\n        total_max += max_score\\n        scored_list.append({\\n            **resp,\\n            \\\"score_awarded\\\": score,\\n            \\\"max_score\\\": max_score\\n        })\\n\\n    overall_pct = round((total_score / total_max) * 100, 2) if total_max > 0 else 0.0\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Total {total_score}/{total_max}, overall {overall_pct}%.\\\")\\n\\n    interview_data[\\\"scored_responses\\\"] = scored_list\\n    interview_data[\\\"total_score\\\"] = total_score\\n    interview_data[\\\"total_max\\\"] = total_max\\n    interview_data[\\\"overall_percentage\\\"] = overall_pct\\n\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, \\\"Completed scoring.\\\")\\n    return interview_data\\n\\ndef generate_evaluation_report(interview_data, report_path, steps_log_path):\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, \\\"Generating final evaluation report.\\\")\\n    total, count = 0.0, 0\\n    with open(report_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as rpt:\\n        rpt.write(\\\"=== Interview Evaluation Report ===\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n        rpt.write(f\\\"Start Time: {interview_data['interview_start']}\\\\n\\\")\\n        rpt.write(f\\\"End Time:   {interview_data['interview_end']}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n        for r in interview_data.get(\\\"scored_responses\\\", []):\\n            rpt.write(f\\\"Q({r['question_id']}): {r['question']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            rpt.write(f\\\"  A: {r['response']}\\\\n\\\")\\n            rpt.write(f\\\"  Score: {r['score_awarded']} / {r['max_score']}\\\\n\\\\n\\\")\\n            total += r['score_awarded']; count += 1\\n        avg = (total / count) if count else 0.0\\n        rpt.write(f\\\"Total Score: {interview_data['total_score']} / {interview_data['total_max']}\\\\n\\\")\\n        rpt.write(f\\\"Overall % : {interview_data['overall_percentage']}%\\\\n\\\")\\n        rpt.write(f\\\"Average per Question: {avg:.2f}\\\\n\\\")\\n    log_step(steps_log_path, f\\\"Saved report to {report_path}.\\\")\\n    return report_path\\n\\ndef parse_args():\\n    p = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\\"Run full interview flow.\\\")\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-j\\\", \\\"--job-description\\\", required=True)\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-r\\\", \\\"--resume\\\", required=True)\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-q\\\", \\\"--questions\\\", required=True, help=\\\"JSON: list of {id,text}\\\")\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-o\\\", \\\"--output\\\", default=\\\"interview_data.json\\\")\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-e\\\", \\\"--candidate-email\\\", required=True)\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"-l\\\", \\\"--steps-log\\\", default=\\\"steps_log.txt\\\")\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"--rubric\\\", default=\\\"scoring_rubric.json\\\")\\n    p.add_argument(\\\"--report\\\", default=\\\"evaluation_report.txt\\\")\\n    return p.parse_args()\\n\\ndef main():\\n    args = parse_args()\\n    _ = analyze_job_description(args.job_description, args.steps_log)\\n    _ = analyze_resume(args.resume, args.steps_log)\\n    data = conduct_technical_interview(\\n        args.job_description, args.resume, args.questions,\\n        args.output, args.candidate_email, args.steps_log\\n    )\\n    scored = score_candidate_responses(data, args.rubric, args.steps_log)\\n    rpt = generate_evaluation_report(scored, args.report, args.steps_log)\\n    print(f\\\"Steps logged to: {args.steps_log}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Report saved to:  {rpt}\\\")\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    main()\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate final evaluation report in .txt format summarizing scores and recommendations\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```text\\n===============================\\nINTERVIEW PROCESS LOG & FINAL REPORT\\n===